content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: TEENRL
      operator: empty
    - name: TEDUR
      operator: empty
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.214
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: Raise an error if TEDUR is null when TEENRL is null
Outcome:
  Message: TEDUR cannot be null when TEENRL is null
  Output Variables:
    - TEENRL
    - TEDUR
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '214'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: Either TEENRL or TEDUR must be present for each Element;
                  both may be present.
                Document: IG v3.1
                Item: Specification
                Section: 7.2.1
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - TRIAL DESIGN
  Domains:
    Include:
      - TE

json.Description: Raise an error if TEDUR is null when TEENRL is null

Outcome.Message: TEDUR cannot be null when TEENRL is null
